-- Chile Says It’s Unlikely to Use Stimulus Measures, Tercera Says
-- B y   R a n d a l l   W o o d s
-- 2012-07-18T13:08:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-18/chile-says-it-s-unlikely-to-use-stimulus-measures-tercera-says.html
Chile’s government probably won’t
need to implement a contingency plan to stimulate growth as long
as the European sovereign-debt crisis doesn’t intensify, La
Tercera  reported  today, citing Deputy Finance Minister Julio Dittborn.  Gross domestic product will expand an estimated 4 percent
to 5 percent this year and next, the Santiago-based  newspaper 
quoted him as saying in an interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Woods in Santiago at 
 rwoods13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  